== Burger Patties ==

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @British beef mince{225%g} in a #mixing
bowl{} with the @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml} and half the @dried Italian herbs{1/4%tsp}. Season
with a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @pepper{}. Combine well using your hands
and shape into one burger patty per person.

> TIP: Try to make the patties the same diameter as the buns.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

== Wedges ==

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop on a
lined #baking tray{}, drizzle over some @olive oil{} and season with salt and
pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out into a single layer and roast on the
top shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

== Salad and Balsamic Dressing ==

Put the @olive oil{}(see ingredients) and @balsamic vinegar{6%ml} in another
#small bowl{}. Keep to one side.

Quarter the @cucumber{1/2} lengthways and chop into 2cm chunks. Chop the
@medium tomato{2} into 2cm pieces, mix together in a #large bowl{}.

== Cooking Burgers ==

Put a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat.
When hot, carefully lay in your burgers and fry until browned on each side
and cooked through.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.
> This should take about 15 mins, carefully turning every 3-4 mins.

== Assembly ==

As the burgers sizzle, cut one slice of @mozzarella{1/2} per person, about
½cm thick. Put the @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp} in a small bowl. Mix in half the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{10%g} and the remaining @dried Italian
herbs{1/4%tsp} (if liked).

When the burgers are almost done, lay a slice of mozzarella on top of each
burger. Sprinkle over the remaining @grated hard Italian style cheese{10%g}.
Add a splash of @water{} to the pan and pop on a #lid{}. Cook for
~{2-3%minutes}. The steam will help melt the cheese! When the wedges are done,
remove them from the oven. Halve the @burger buns{2} and put on another baking
tray, warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once everything is ready, spread some of the herby ketchup on each half of the
buns. Sandwich the burgers between the buns and serve alongside plenty of
wedges. The salad is up to you: kids may just want plain tomato and cucumber,
but for a more interesting side, toss the tomato and cucumber in the balsamic
dressing with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. When serving, tear over the
remaining mozzarella. Tuck in!